The paper deals with gait recognition using machine learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of linear discriminant analysis and maximum margin criterion, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of appropriate classifiers, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
